<div class="container hz-content">
        <div class="row">
            <div class="col-sm-offset-2 col-sm-7">
                <center>
                    <h1>Submit a query</h1>
                </center>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div id="flash_msg">submit successfully!!!</div>
        <div class="form-horizontal hz-form" role="form">
            <div class="form-group" id="email_input">
                <label class="col-sm-2 control-label">Email</label>
                <div class="col-sm-7 hz-inline">
                    <div id="email_sign" class="input-group-addon">@</div>
                    <input type="email" class="form-control" placeholder="Please leave an email address">
                    <span class="input-indicator"></span>
                </div>
                <div class="col-sm-3">
                    We'll send you a notification when job's done
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="form-group" id="data_input">
                <label class="col-sm-2 control-label">Enter data</label>
                <div class="col-sm-7">
                    <textarea class="form-control" name="inputData" placeholder="Please enter your data with ANNOVAR format here..." rows="7"></textarea>
                    <span class="input-indicator"></span>
                    <button id="submit_text" class="btn btn-default">Submit text</button>
                </div>
                <div class="col-sm-3">
                    <div class="hz-bar">
                        <span>What is <a class="annovar" href="http://www.openbioinformatics.org/annovar/">ANNOVAR</a> input format
                            <button id="an_ex_btn" type="button" class="btn btn-sm btn-link ex-btn" data-toggle="popover" data-content="This format is denoted by the author of ANNOVAR package. The format is essentially Tab or Space deliminated table with five columns indicating 'chromosome id', 'start coordinate of the mutation (1 based)', 'end coordinate of the mutation (1 based)', 'reference allele', 'alternative allele'. Example of one row: '1	12919840	12919840	T	C'">(?)</button>
                        </span>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="form-group">
                <label class="col-sm-2 control-label">
                    <span class="hz-label">Or you can</span>
                </label>
                <div class="col-sm-7">
                    <div id="file_dropzone">
                        <div>
                            <span class="btn btn-default hz-file-btn">
                                <span><i class="glyphicon glyphicon-paperclip"></i>
                                </span>
                                <input id="file_upload" type="file" name="inputFile">
                            </span>
                            <span>Add or drag & drop your file with VCF/ANNOVAR format here</span>
                        </div>
                    </div>
		
                    <div id="upload_progress" class="progress">
                        <div class="progress-bar progress-bar-info" role="progressbar" style="width: 0%;">
                            <span class="sr-only"></span>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <button id="submit_file" class="btn btn-default">Submit file</button>
                </div>
        	<div class="col-sm-3">
			<div class="hz-bar">
				<span>What is <a href="http://www.1000genomes.org/wiki/Analysis/Variant%20Call%20Format/vcf-variant-call-format-version-41">VCF</a> input format <button id="vcf_ex_btn" type="button" class="btn btn-sm btn-link ex-btn" data-toggle="popover" data-content="The Variant Call Format (VCF) specifies the format of a text file used in bioinformatics for storing gene sequence variations. Please click the hyperlink 'VCF' for more details.">(?)</button></span>		
			</div>
		</div>  
	  </div>
	  
        </div>
        <script src="assets/upload.js"></script>
</div>
